<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="578" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d578">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/1519²⁄₄</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to
                            the British Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Halifax</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-14">December 14,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Halifax</hi>: Here is a message to General
                        Chiang Kai-Shek<note n="63" xml:id="d578fn63">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_751">p. 751</ref>.</note>
                        and a similar message from me to Mr. Stalin.<note n="64" xml:id="d578fn64">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> They are self-explanatory.</p>
                    <p>I hope you will ask London if they will go ahead with the holding of the
                        Singapore conference and also instruct your people in Chungking and Moscow
                        to take part in the proposed meetings as soon as they are held by Chiang
                        Kai-Shek and Stalin. I assume, of course, that Australia and New Zealand
                        will be represented in Singapore.</p>
                    <p>Always sincerely,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Franklin D. Roosevelt</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>